{"title_page": "Andr\u00e9s Pav\u00f3n", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Andr\u00e9s Pav\u00f3n\n| image       =\n| caption     = \n| birthname   = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1962|7|21}}\n| birth_place = [[Col\u00f3n Department (Honduras)|Col\u00f3n]], [[Honduras]]\n| age         = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place =\n| education   =\n| occupation  = Politician\n| party       = [[Democratic Unification Party|UD]]/[[FAPER]]\n| alias       = \n| gender      = \n| status      =\n| title       =\n| family      =\n| spouse      = Ritzy Alm\u00e9ndarez\n| children    = 3\n| relatives   =\n| religion    = \n| salary      =\n| networth    =\n| credits     = \n| agent       =\n| URL         =\n}}\n\n'''Andr\u00e9s Pav\u00f3n Murillo''' (born 21 July 1962) is a [[Honduran people|Honduran]] politician and Human Rights activist.<ref>{{cite news|title=Perfiles de los candidatos a la presidencia de Honduras |url=http://tiempo.hn/portada/noticias/perfiles-de-los-candidatos-a-la-presidencia-de-honduras |accessdate=17 November 2013 |newspaper=Diario Tiempo |date=7 November 2013 |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123065242/http://www.tiempo.hn/portada/noticias/perfiles-de-los-candidatos-a-la-presidencia-de-honduras |archivedate=23 November 2013 }}</ref> He ran unsuccessfully as a presidential candidate for the [[2013 Honduran general election|2013 general election]] representing the [[Democratic Unification Party|UD]]/[[FAPER]] alliance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Andr\u00e9s Pav\u00f3n es el candidato presidencial de FAPER y UD |url=http://www.latribuna.hn/2013/05/23/andres-pavon-es-el-candidato-presidencial-de-faper-y-ud/ |accessdate=17 November 2013 |newspaper=[[La Tribuna (Honduras)|La Tribuna]] |date=23 May 2013 |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140514131443/http://www.latribuna.hn/2013/05/23/andres-pavon-es-el-candidato-presidencial-de-faper-y-ud/ |archivedate=14 May 2014 }}</ref> and former President of the [[Committee for the Defense of Human Rights in Honduras]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pavon, Andres}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Col\u00f3n Department (Honduras)]]\n[[Category:Candidates for President of Honduras]]\n[[Category:Honduran activists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Andr\u00e9s Pav\u00f3n\n| image       =\n| caption     = \n| birthname   = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1962|7|21}}\n| birth_place = [[Col\u00f3n Department (Honduras)|Col\u00f3n]], [[Honduras]]\n| age         = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place =\n| education   =\n| occupation  = Politician\n| party       = [[Democratic Unification Party|UD]]/[[FAPER]]\n| alias       = \n| gender      = \n| status      =\n| title       =\n| family      =\n| spouse      = Ritzy Alm\u00e9ndarez\n| children    = 3\n| relatives   =\n| religion    = \n| salary      =\n| networth    =\n| credits     = \n| agent       =\n| URL         =\n}}\n\n'''Andr\u00e9s Pav\u00f3n Murillo''' (born 21 July 1962) is a [[Honduran people|Honduran]] politician and Human Rights activist.<ref>{{cite news|title=Perfiles de los candidatos a la presidencia de Honduras |url=http://tiempo.hn/portada/noticias/perfiles-de-los-candidatos-a-la-presidencia-de-honduras |accessdate=17 November 2013 |newspaper=Diario Tiempo |date=7 November 2013 |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123065242/http://www.tiempo.hn/portada/noticias/perfiles-de-los-candidatos-a-la-presidencia-de-honduras |archivedate=23 November 2013 }}</ref> He ran unsuccessfully as a presidential candidate for the [[2013 Honduran general election|2013 general election]] representing the [[Democratic Unification Party|UD]]/[[FAPER]] alliance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Andr\u00e9s Pav\u00f3n es el candidato presidencial de FAPER y UD |url=http://www.latribuna.hn/2013/05/23/andres-pavon-es-el-candidato-presidencial-de-faper-y-ud/ |accessdate=17 November 2013 |newspaper=[[La Tribuna]] |date=23 May 2013 |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140514131443/http://www.latribuna.hn/2013/05/23/andres-pavon-es-el-candidato-presidencial-de-faper-y-ud/ |archivedate=14 May 2014 }}</ref> and former President of the [[Committee for the Defense of Human Rights in Honduras]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pavon, Andres}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Col\u00f3n Department (Honduras)]]\n[[Category:Candidates for President of Honduras]]\n[[Category:Honduran activists]]\n", "name_user": "Tassedethe", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 - Repaired 1 link to disambiguation page -(You can help)-La Tribuna", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9s_Pav%C3%B3n"}
