ez]] |accessdate=22 June 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 18 July 2019 || {{flagicon|HON}} [[Gerson Rodas]] || {{flagicon|HON}} Platense || {{flagicon|HON}} Honduras Progreso || <ref>{{cite web |title=OFICIAL: Gerson Rodas es anunciado como el nuevo jugador del Honduras Progreso |url=https://www.diez.hn/liganacionaldehonduras/1303013-498/gerson-rondas-nuevo-jugador-honduras-progreso-mercado-fichajes-liga-nacional |website=Diez.hn |publisher=[[La Prensa (Honduras)|Diario Diez]] |accessdate=18 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 22 July 2019 || {{flagicon|TRI}} [[Jerrel Britto]] || {{flagicon|HON}} Platense || {{flagicon|HON}} Honduras Progreso || \n|-\n| 9 August 2019 || {{flagicon|HON}} [[Emilio Izaguirre]] || {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] || {{flagicon|HON}} [[F.C. Motagua|Motagua]] || <ref>https://www.eveningtimes.co.uk/sport/17831548.ex-celtic-star-emilio-izaguirre-re-signs-hometown-club-motagua-failing-land-mls-deal/</ref>\n|-\n| 4 September 2019 || {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Evgeni Kabaev]] || {{flagicon|EST}} [[FCI Levadia Tallinn|Levadia Tallinn]] || {{flagicon|HON}} [[C.D. Real de Minas|Real de Minas]] || <ref>{{cite web |title=\u00a1Fichaje europeo! Evgeny Kabaev, de pelear la Bota de Oro con CR7 al Real de Minas de Honduras |url=https://www.diez.hn/liganacionaldehonduras/1315966-498/evgeny-kabaev-delantero-ruso-nuevo-fichaje-real-de-minas-peleo-bota-de-oro-cristiano-ronaldo |website=Diez.hn |publisher=[[La Prensa (Honduras)|Diario Diez]] |accessdate=4 September 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Winter transfers===\n\n===Liga Nacional===\n{{main|2019\u201320 Honduran Liga Nacional}}\n\n===Liga de Ascenso===\n{{main|2019\u201320 Honduran Liga Nacional de Ascenso}}\n\n===Major League===\n{{main|2019\u201320 Honduran Major League}}\n\n===Honduran Cup===\n{{main|2019 Honduran Cup}}\n\n===Honduran Supercup===\n{{main|2020 Honduran Supercup}}\n\n===CONCACAF Champions League===\n{{main|2020 CONCACAF Champions League}}\n{{#lst:2020 CONCACAF Champions League|Bracket}}\n\n===CONCACAF League===\n{{main|2019 CONCACAF League}}\n{{#lst:2019 CONCACAF League|Bracket}}\n\n===Other matches===\nTBA\n\n==Deaths==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Date !! Name !! Born !! Notes\n|-\n| 11 August 2019 || {{flagicon|HON}} [[Walter Mart\u00ednez (footballer)|Walter Mart\u00ednez]] || 28 March 1982 (aged 37) || Former [[Honduras national football team]] player.  Heart failure.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fallece el futbolista hondure\u00f1o Walter 'Pery' Mart\u00ednez en Estados Unidos |url=https://www.laprensa.hn/deportes/1309284-410/fallece-el-futbolista-hondure%C3%B1o-walter-pery-mart%C3%ADnez-en-estados-unidos-infarto |website=LaPrensa.hn |publisher=[[La Prensa (Honduras)|La Prensa]] |accessdate=11 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 27 August 2019 || {{flagicon|HON}} [[Mario Caballero]] || 23 August 1943 (aged 76) || Former [[C.D. Marath\u00f3n]] player.  [[Cardiac arrest]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Muere Mario 'Cofra' Caballero, integrante de la 'trinca infernal' de Marath\u00f3n |url=https://www.diez.hn/liganacionaldehonduras/1313641-498/muere-mario-cofra-caballero-exfutbolista-honduras-marathon-trinca-infernal |website=Diez.hn |publisher=[[La Prensa (Honduras)|Diario Diez]] |accessdate=27 August 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2 September 2019 || {{flagicon|HON}} [[Morris Garden]] || \u2013 || Former [[C.D.S. Vida]] player.<ref>{{cite web |title=Morris Garden: Falleci\u00f3 ex leyenda del Vida |url=https://www.diariomas.hn/2019/09/02/morris-garden-fallecio-ex-leyenda-del-vida/ |website=DiarioMas.hn |publisher=[[La Tribuna (Honduras)|La Tribuna]] |accessdate=2 September 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 5 October 2019 || {{flagicon|NCA}} [[Roger Mayorga]] || 10 July 1946 (aged 73) || Former [[F.C. Motagua]] goalkeeper.  [[Myocardial infarction|Heart attack]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Muere Roger Mayorga m\u00edtico portero nicarag\u00fcense ex de Motagua |url=https://www.diariomas.hn/2019/10/05/muere-roger-mayorga-mitico-portero-nicaraguense-ex-de-motagua/ |website=DiarioMas.hn |publisher=[[La Tribuna (Honduras)|La Tribuna]] |accessdate=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 7 January 2020 || {{flagicon|HON}} [[Geovany Alarc\u00f3n]] || 1965 or 1966 (aged 54) || Former [[Real C.D. Espa\u00f1a]] and [[C.D. Victoria]] footballer.  Cancer.\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 in Honduran football}}\n{{2019\u201320 in North and Central America, and Caribbean football (CONCACAF)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2019-20 in Honduran football}}\n[[Category:2019\u201320 in Honduran football| ]]\n[[Category:2019 in association football|Honduras]]\n[[Category:2020 in association football|Honduras]]\n[[Category:2019 in Honduras|Football]]\n[[Category:2020 in Honduras|Football]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football country season\n| country    = Honduras\n| season     = 2019\u201320\n| division1  = [[2019\u201320 Honduran Liga Nacional|Liga Nacional]]\n| champions1 = Apertura:<br>TBD<br>Clausura:<br>TBD\n| division2  = [[2019\u201320 Honduran Liga Nacional de Ascenso|Liga de Ascenso]]\n| champions2 = Apertura:<br>TBD<br>Clausura:<br>TBD\n| division3  = [[2019\u201320 Honduran Major League|Major League]]\n| champions3 = \n| division4  = \n| champions4 = \n| division5  = \n| champions5 = \n| domestic   = [[2019 Honduran Cup|Honduran Cup]]\n| dchampions = TBD\n| leaguecup  = \n| lchampions = \n| supercup   = [[2020 Honduran Supercup|Honduran Supercup]]\n| schampions = TBD\n| prevseason = 2018\u201319\n| nextseason = 2020\u201321\n| flagicon   = yes\n}}\n\nThe '''2019\u201320 season''' is the 72nd season of competitive association [[Association football in Honduras|football in Honduras]].\n\n==National teams==\n===Senior team===\n====CONCACAF Nations League====\n{{main|2019\u201320 CONCACAF Nations League}}\n{{2019\u201320 CONCACAF Nations League A group tables|Group C|show_matches=yes|only_pld_pts=no_hide_class_rules}}\n\n====Other matches====\n{{main|Honduras national football team results (2010\u201319)}}\n{{main|Honduras national football team results (2020\u201329)}}\n\n===Olympic team===\n====CON