i}}\n| {{flag|Kelantan}}\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Adham Baba]]\n| [[United Malays National Organisation]] ([[Barisan Nasional]])\n| {{pseat|Tenggara}}\n| {{flag|Johor}}\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Ahmad Amzad Mohamed]]\n| [[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party]] ([[Gagasan Sejahtera]])\n| {{pseat|Kuala Terengganu}}\n| {{flag|Terengganu}}\n|-\n| 6\n| [[Ahmad Fadhli Shaari]]\n| [[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party]] ([[Gagasan Sejahtera]])\n| {{pseat|Pasir Mas}}\n| {{flag|Kelantan}}\n|-\n| 7\n| [[Ahmad Johnie Zawawi]]\n| [[Parti Pesaka Bumiputera Bersatu|United Bumiputera Heritage Party]] ([[Gabungan Parti Sarawak]])\n| {{pseat|Igan}}\n| {{flag|Sarawak}}\n|-\n| 8\n| [[Ahmad Maslan]]\n| [[United Malays National Organisation]] ([[Barisan Nasional]])\n| {{pseat|Pontian}}\n| {{flag|Johor}}\n|-\n| 9\n| [[Ahmad Marzuk Shaari]]\n| [[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party]] ([[Gagasan Sejahtera]])\n| {{pseat|Pengkalan Chepa}}\n| {{flag|Kelantan}}\n|-\n| 10\n| [[Ahmad Tarmizi Sulaiman]]\n| [[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party]] ([[Gagasan Sejahtera]])\n| {{pseat|Sik}}\n| {{flag|Kedah}}\n|-\n| 11\n| [[Alexander Nanta Linggi]]\n| [[Parti Pesaka Bumiputera Bersatu|United Bumiputera Heritage Party]] ([[Gabungan Parti Sarawak]])\n| {{pseat|Kapit}}\n| {{flag|Sarawak}}\n|-\n| 12\n| [[Annuar Musa]]\n| [[United Malays National Organisation]] ([[Barisan Nasional]])\n| {{pseat|Ketereh}}\n| {{flag|Kelantan}}\n|-\n| 13\n| [[Anyi Ngau]]\n| [[Progressive Democratic Party (Malaysia)|Progressive Democratic Party]] ([[Gabungan Parti Sarawak]])\n| {{pseat|Baram}}\n| {{flag|Sarawak}}\n|-\n| 14\n| [[Awang Hashim]]\n| [[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party]] ([[Gagasan Sejahtera]])\n| {{pseat|Pendang}}\n| {{flag|Kedah}}\n|-\n| 15\n| [[Bung Moktar Radin]]\n| [[United Malays National Organisation]] ([[Barisan Nasional]])\n| {{pseat|Kinabatangan}}\n| {{flag|Sabah}}\n|-\n| 16\n| [[Che Abdullah Mat Nawi]]\n| [[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party]] ([[Gagasan Sejahtera]])\n| {{pseat|Tumpat}}\n| {{flag|Kelantan}}\n|-\n| 17\n| [[Che Alias Hamid]]\n| [[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party]]