an]])\n| {{pseat|Sepang}}\n| {{flag|Selangor}}\n|-\n| 76\n| [[Mohammadin Ketapi]]\n| [[Sabah Heritage Party]]\n| {{pseat|Silam}}\n| {{flag|Sabah}}\n|-\n| 77\n| [[Mordi Bimol]]\n| [[Democratic Action Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Mas Gading}}\n| {{flag|Sarawak}}\n|-\n| 78\n| [[Muhammad Bakhtiar Wan Chik]]\n| [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|People's Justice Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Balik Pulau}}\n| {{flag|Penang}}\n|-\n| 79\n| [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]\n| [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Pagoh}}\n| {{flag|Johor}}\n|-\n| 80\n| [[Mujahid Yusof Rawa]]\n| [[National Trust Party (Malaysia)|National Trust Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Parit Buntar}}\n| {{flag|Perak}}\n|-\n| 81\n| [[Mukhriz Mahathir]]\n| [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Jerlun}}\n| {{flag|Kedah}}\n|-\n| 82\n| [[Mustapa Mohamed]]\n| [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Jeli}}\n| {{flag|Kelantan}}\n|-\n| 83\n| [[Natrah Ismail]]\n| [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|People's Justice Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Sekijang}}\n| {{flag|Johor}}\n|-\n| 84\n| [[Nga Kor Ming]]\n| [[Democratic Action Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Teluk Intan}}\n| {{flag|Perak}}\n|-\n| 85\n| [[Ngeh Koo Ham]]\n| [[Democratic Action Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Beruas}}\n| {{flag|Perak}}\n|-\n| 86\n| [[Nik Nazmi|Nik Nazmi Nik Ahmad]]\n| [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|People's Justice Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Setiawangsa}}\n| {{flag|Kuala Lumpur}}\n|-\n| 87\n| [[Noor Azmi Ghazali]]\n| [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Bagan Serai}}\n| {{flag|Perak}}\n|-\n| 88\n| [[Noorita Sual]]\n| [[Democratic Action Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Tenom}}\n| {{flag|Sabah}}\n|-\n| 89\n| [[Nor Azrina Surip]]\n| [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|People's Justice Party]] ([[Pakatan Harapan]])\n| {{pseat|Merbok}}